\PYG{l+s+sd}{\PYGZdq{}\PYGZdq{}\PYGZdq{}}
\PYG{l+s+sd}{Plot \PYGZdq{}heatmap\PYGZdq{} figures for our data.}

\PYG{l+s+sd}{It is assumed that script is run in a directory containing *.dat file with}
\PYG{l+s+sd}{specific names:}
\PYG{l+s+sd}{  MODEL\PYGZus{}BORN\PYGZus{}PARAM\PYGZus{}idNUM.dat}
\PYG{l+s+sd}{where MODEL is either \PYGZsq{}sun\PYGZsq{}, \PYGZsq{}sn\PYGZsq{} or \PYGZsq{}earth\PYGZsq{}. The BORN is either \PYGZsq{}in\PYGZsq{} (inside)}
\PYG{l+s+sd}{or \PYGZsq{}out\PYGZsq{} (outside, pass through regime), the PARAM is either \PYGZsq{}s12\PYGZsq{}, \PYGZsq{}s13\PYGZsq{},}
\PYG{l+s+sd}{\PYGZsq{}par1\PYGZsq{} or \PYGZsq{}par2\PYGZsq{} (may be more), the NUM is serial number (beginning from 0).}

\PYG{l+s+sd}{\PYGZdq{}\PYGZdq{}\PYGZdq{}}

